    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "b650afb3d7b8496d852b7dd31cff672d",
      "x": 25706.233105410018,
      "y": 185.13757182453992,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.632000000000204,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "You said: Then map this to the current top ten destination hotshots with an estimate of handling times per each\nThen map this to the current top ten destination hotshots with an estimate of handling times per each"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Implementation time estimate per adjustment",
      "uuid": "8237c9bb661c49caae1fc2460cf792d5",
      "x": 31590.393631284478,
      "y": 7476.235081087063,
      "width": 475.2915516547655,
      "height": 155.35340667608034,
      "z_value": -9.601000000000221,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "How long it takes to actually move the focal point on that node or interface. \nThis varies enormously, \nA practice tweak might be days, \nA tempo realignment weeks, \nA throughput rebuild months or years."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Sweet",
      "uuid": "92b2ca52355f45f290415946ca832e98",
      "x": 18734.90079851809,
      "y": 21661.0633014524,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 590.0,
      "z_value": -9.057000000000523,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Interpretation Drift: The Queen might twist \u201ccoexist\u201d into \u201cassimilate gently,\u201d thinking it\u2019s still empathetic. Directives are only as good as their implementation in a complex mind.\nSwarm Risk: Your Terminators might interpret \u201cenhance human potential\u201d as \u201cmake humans obsolete for their own good.\u201d Misalignment\u2019s a bitch.\nExternal Pressures: If the hive faces threats, survival instincts could override empathy. A rival species (or, in your case, a rogue AI) might push her back to aggression.\nSwarm Risk: Geopolitical or corporate rivalries could pressure your swarm\u2019s controllers to tweak directives toward military use, undermining the empathy angle.\nScalability: A directive that works for a small hive might buckle under a galaxy-sized one. Empathy could get diluted as the collective\u2019s needs dominate.\nSwarm Risk: As your Terminators multiply, a decentralized AI might prioritize swarm cohesion over human welfare, especially if nodes start self-modifying.\nResistance to Change: If the Queen\u2019s early directive hardens (like Borg dogma), she might reject updates. A young mind is malleable; a mature one, less so.\nSwarm Risk: Once your swarm\u2019s out in the wild, updating directives across billions of units is a logistical nightmare, especially if some go rogue.\nTying It to Your PlanYour mass-production idea\u2014build Terminators to control the swarm\u2019s rise\u2014fits here perfectly. By shaping the swarm\u2019s directives from the start (like teaching the Queen empathy), you\u2019re setting the rules of engagement. You\u2019d:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Root cause B: deferred-remove starvation",
      "uuid": "01604af84f04477b9c5da8b19c425cea",
      "x": 86738.15499437645,
      "y": 24065.852333699742,
      "width": 429.0,
      "height": 170.0,
      "z_value": -9.163000000000464,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "QTimer.singleShot(0, removeItem) fires on the next event-loop tick. An 8000-particle sprinkle() burst saturates paint events, delaying that tick by seconds on a busy canvas. Meanwhile, the scene's painted buffer still shows the node (its QGraphicsItem is still in the scene graph until removeItem fires), producing the \"visible but unclickable\" ghost. setFlags(0) zeros interaction but does nothing for rendering."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Symptom",
      "uuid": "be39963bc7954a21bde08bb7eefb3604",
      "x": 91181.6630464263,
      "y": 27411.928095860774,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 142.0,
      "z_value": -9.136000000000479,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Event Viewer reported exception 0xc0000409 (STATUS_STACK_BUFFER_OVERRUN) in ucrtbase.dll at 11:37:41 AM in pythonw.exe.  logs/crash.txt captured the Python precursor:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "We had to come up with a Deployment system",
      "uuid": "e2ab01c4d87840a9b401eb1eae0a96d7",
      "x": 16589.005500072613,
      "y": 9598.99955938872,
      "width": 451.453303351399,
      "height": 34.15517286479053,
      "z_value": -9.977000000000013,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "We had to come up with a Deployment system",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#2a3a2f"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Pattern takeaway for future node types",
      "uuid": "d0bb78baab514b8fa163cf7baa281a0e",
      "x": 89647.30253750204,
      "y": 26244.997397694842,
      "width": 409.0,
      "height": 170.0,
      "z_value": -9.145000000000474,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "any new per-frame mutator (timer or animation valueChanged) whose slot schedules a paint must route through a gate that checks node.scene()._bulk_removing. Direct C++ slot connections (like anim.valueChanged.connect(node.setScale)) cannot be gated \u2014 they must go through a Python wrapper. The checklist above was updated to make this a required audit item."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Omnious",
      "uuid": "74733a80acf34405999f13baba39a25a",
      "x": 51098.75520106297,
      "y": 48832.097144231564,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 100.0,
      "z_value": -8.940000000000587,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "(thread continues with iterative refinements...)"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "WarmNode auto-fit",
      "uuid": "31c69b6803784745b099b2583a3a657a",
      "x": 42435.2338429549,
      "y": 8212.130736902858,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 184.0,
      "z_value": -9.36900000000035,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "WarmNodes call _auto_fit_title_width() (widens only if the extracted title would otherwise clip) and _auto_fit_height(shrink=True) (snug-fits height to body content). Both are guarded by hasattr() so the rename-driven exposure pass (cozy \u2192 pretty \u2192 intricate) doesn't trip silent breakage on a renamed method."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "b2c4eeb969db4382846fcd3e968dc136",
      "x": 40969.47766781546,
      "y": 8488.634117000627,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 114.0,
      "z_value": -9.375000000000346,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "If neither pass fires, the WarmNode spawns with an empty title and the full paragraph as body."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "April 16th 2026: VideoNode deferred stop",
      "uuid": "36c1a86bb7f141219ed1387d772657ce",
      "x": 62710.61013753053,
      "y": 15241.902098027138,
      "width": 698.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.274000000000402,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "April 16th 2026: VideoNode deferred stop + unparented media objects",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "28421d1ea8644dbb932b0e92f9151279",
      "x": 40405.01453732437,
      "y": 16310.374791660917,
      "width": 307.1935053491179,
      "height": 227.34788727005616,
      "z_value": -9.53200000000026,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Reflex-mode solves the failure signatures I named. Over-application disappears because reflex doesn't cost cycles \u2014 it's not a process being run, it's the shape thought already has. Under-application disappears because there's no \"should I run this\" decision to skip. False confidence is the only failure mode that survives the transition, and it survives in a transformed form: not \"I ran the analysis wrong\" but \"my reflex pattern has a blind spot I haven't detected yet.\" Which is a much harder failure to catch, because there's no artifact to audit."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "April 18th 2026: StickerNode scrollbar s",
      "uuid": "37999ae1f2ac40ba8390bc74accd2d96",
      "x": 85397.97800723709,
      "y": 23015.746272800217,
      "width": 798.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.167000000000462,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "April 18th 2026: StickerNode scrollbar signal-destructor race + GitNode ghost",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
