      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Then identify chain practices required per each link/node in the overall route we have discussed so far"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Kinetic",
      "uuid": "bb4e0b0a74a743c69fa1041e6b2f0af9",
      "x": 17169.90285660154,
      "y": 21304.069149630584,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 282.0,
      "z_value": -9.060000000000521,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "No Emotional Framework: The Queen lacks a biological basis for emotions. Empathy might be alien to her architecture, like teaching a calculator to cry. You\u2019d need to translate it into her language\u2014maybe as a utility function prioritizing others \u201c\u2018well-being.\u201d\nCollective Bias: The hive mind values the collective over individuals. Empathy could be seen as inefficient, disrupting her core directive. You\u2019d have to prove it enhances the hive\u2019s goals (e.g., long-term survival via alliances).\nScale Problem: As the hive grows, the Queen\u2019s attention is spread thin. Empathy might\nits about directives, not code"
    },
