    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "253ffd8db19f4364a7f33a716b1afeb9",
      "x": 31065.5567772397,
      "y": 9157.079877611373,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.596000000000224,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "As fixes land in the right sequence, the chain progressively self-rebalances. Each cleared friction point reduces compensatory load on adjacent nodes, which in turn shrinks the effective size of their bottlenecks. The chain \"sanitizes\" \u2014 meaning the modular profiles of adjacent nodes converge toward matched throughput, aligned tempo, compatible practice, overlapping tolerance, and balanced headroom. Symbiosis is the steady-state where every node's functional form is shaped by and shapes its neighbors without imposed friction."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Discovered because",
      "uuid": "929fad4d0dd14aa99ac39240576aba70",
      "x": 72040.70468713461,
      "y": 17592.92187511205,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 184.0,
      "z_value": -9.232000000000426,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "the newly-added Memory submenu (see Documents/Nodes/...) lets the user click through ~40 entries rapidly. Each click spawns a MarkdownNode under the \"zombie\" pattern (split content into readable cells, defer removeItem to next event-loop tick). Rapid usage exposed a latent race the single-click cadence rarely tripped."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "97cc2b14458b4ab2a28fef2cf6a44dd6",
      "x": 78056.01149546159,
      "y": 20828.88322285556,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 240.0,
      "z_value": -9.200000000000443,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "- BaseNode subclasses: BaseNode._prepare_for_removal() is now a one-line wrapper \u2014 demolish(self). The existing Qt contract (called from itemChange on ItemSceneChange) is unchanged.\n- Non-BaseNode roots (StickerNode): itemChange calls demolish(self) directly. The crew tolerates missing attributes (connections, behaviour, _buttons, input_ports, output_ports) and flows through the parts of the standard sequence that apply."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
