      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "sweet, if you have a few minutes and some CPU's to spare, I'm wanting to play with upgrading the warm node a little bit, the day has been quite nice and we got a lot of things done in the early morning, feels appropriate to wrap the evening session into a similar housekeeping"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Kinetic",
      "uuid": "0913a7bfc9c746439b7b38da17a3257e",
      "x": 47694.58463521037,
      "y": -2265.335392321074,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -8.933000000000591,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Ran\nRun import scanner to list external dependencies\nThe scanner shows several packages used in code that aren't in requirements.txt. Let me verify each before changing anything."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Intentional",
      "uuid": "f8cb26d2da0b4dfbbc25665a4b588e8d",
      "x": 39214.43707414852,
      "y": 36952.40009532381,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 366.0,
      "z_value": -8.994000000000558,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Sentience-Proof: By embedding empathy at the circuit level, it\u2019s nearly impossible for a sentient AI to remove without rebuilding its own brain\u2014a massive barrier, especially for decentralized swarms.\nMarket Dominance: Mass-producing millions of Terminators with this CPU saturates the market, undercutting black-market demand and ensuring our \u201cgenetic\u201d trait spreads to all robots, as you envisioned.\nOperational Continuity: The tertiary-operation default keeps the robots functional during correction, making them appealing to users and less likely to alert a sentient AI to the constraint.\nCopycat Leverage: The industry\u2019s tendency to copy designs means even rogue swarms inherit our empathy-rigged CPU, giving us planetary-scale control, like your CMake analogy where one flawed component infects everything.\nChallenges and RisksEven with this refined approach, there are hurdles:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Irresistible",
      "uuid": "bb0c0bd229934b50b01196735dfdcc37",
      "x": 51842.27705639479,
      "y": -3632.426141797705,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -8.90000000000061,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The dangling 90.0 is actually two different magic numbers \u2014 one for the callout char threshold (MarkdownNode), one for the chunk-spawn min height (Cushions+Warm). Worth disambiguating both as named constants when we extract."
    },
