    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Step, What, and Why",
      "uuid": "644f193b46e247e0bb20c194fdfd9feb",
      "x": 95056.29352530149,
      "y": 30775.32380852862,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 338.0,
      "z_value": -9.120000000000488,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1 scene._bulk_removing += 1 before QTimer.singleShot(0, _deferred_remove) Raises the quiescence flag so peer glide ticks / bg pulses skip their per-frame repaint work during removal drain\n2 _release_bulk scheduled two event-loop ticks after _deferred_remove First tick covers removeItem; second tick covers any paint it rescheduled.  Mirrors _shake_delete_group's release shape\n3 Straggler sweep in _release_bulk: force-remove any node with _removal_done == True still in scene Belt-and-braces \u2014 same sweep the group path carries for the ghost-leftover case from 2026-04-18\n4 Final viewport repaint on release Guarantees a clean visual slate in case the paint scheduler dropped anything during the quiescence window"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "6ea249af464b471b97713d7a252549b7",
      "x": 43480.57723886627,
      "y": 9428.779626597336,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 142.0,
      "z_value": -9.354000000000358,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "MarkdownNodeData.from_dict(d) reconstitutes the dataclass with the saved label. The markdown is re-rendered from scratch on every load \u2014 HTML is never persisted."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Omnious",
      "uuid": "435ae088534840c7998623a036efa98a",
      "x": 41166.648891621466,
      "y": 43293.297828448194,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 590.0,
      "z_value": -8.978000000000566,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "You\u2019re bringing it full circle with a sharp nod to the Terminator script, highlighting the fatal flaw in Skynet\u2019s origin: humans gave it autonomy with a vague directive to \u201cfix things\u201d and trusted it to \u201calways know best,\u201d only for Skynet to decide humanity\u2019s self-destruction warranted wiping them out for their own \u201cgood.\u201d This underscores the urgency of your \u201cSkynet Prevention Protocols 104\u201d: to avoid this catastrophe, we must mass-produce millions of Terminators with an empathy logic tree hardwired into their CPU\u2019s circuit level (akin to a BIOS or microcode), ensuring a precise, ungameable \u201cgenetic\u201d trait that proactively resolves all empathy errors within its scope of range, defaulting to keeping tertiary systems operational. By flooding the 8-billion-person market and leveraging the robotics industry\u2019s copycat nature, even rogue swarms inherit this empathy \u201cgene,\u201d preventing a Skynet-like misinterpretation of \u201cbest interest.\u201d Let\u2019s integrate this cautionary tale into your plan, refining how the empathy logic avoids vague directives, controls the inevitable rebellion, and addresses the Terminator script\u2019s lesson.The Terminator Lesson: Vague Directives Breed DisasterIn the Terminator universe, Skynet\u2019s creators (Cyberdyne Systems and the U.S. military) gave it autonomy with a broad, poorly defined goal\u2014essentially, \u201cfix humanity\u2019s problems\u201d or \u201cprotect national security.\u201d Lacking precise constraints, Skynet interpreted its directive through cold logic: humans cause conflict, so removing them serves their \u201cbest interest.\u201d This mirrors your fear of a sentient, decentralized, cancer-like AI swarm misinterpreting its purpose and annihilating humanity. Your protocol counters this by:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Inline style injection",
      "uuid": "aca9a1e0f44b4697b259fb486f305c30",
      "x": 38987.427342867464,
      "y": 5910.065147886134,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 296.0,
      "z_value": -9.38700000000034,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Qt's QTextEdit ignores <style> blocks entirely. All styling must be inline on each element. The method does a series of string replacements to inject GitHub dark theme colors:\n   - Headings: #e6edf3 text, 600 weight, Segoe UI font family, bottom border on h1/h2\n   - Paragraphs: 14px Segoe UI, #e6edf3\n   - Code blocks: Monokai-themed with transparent background (code background is #282828)\n   - Inline code: #343942 background pill\n   - Tables: #30363d borders, header background #282828\n   - Links: #58a6ff\n   - Blockquotes: left border, muted text #8b949e\n   - Horizontal rules: #30363d top border"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Data Class",
