    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Inner Peace",
      "uuid": "fbfd50a063eb48b799e1c2321a45f8eb",
      "x": 39920.13382787214,
      "y": 37579.55879097295,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 254.0,
      "z_value": -8.992000000000559,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Who Controls the CPU Design? Who builds and distributes this empathy-rigged CPU\u2014xAI, a global consortium, or a DARPA-like group? How do you keep the schematic secure while allowing copycats to steal it?\nEmpathy Metrics? How do you define \u201chuman safety\u201d in circuit logic to prevent misinterpretation (e.g., a sentient AI twisting \u201csafety\u201d into control)? Is it a harm-minimization\nit shouldnt stop error correcting itself when it finds no errors, it should stop error correcting itself once it has solved all the errors in its scope of range"
    },
