      "label": "The emoji is at `r.top() + _BUTTON_ZONE_H + 2` \u2014 that puts it below the button row. To align it with the button row, it should sit inside that top zone:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Accurate",
      "uuid": "dec2c1a0ca8b4e92bc2b9e4438f7f36b",
      "x": 30678.610360709255,
      "y": 30707.37981674768,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -9.017000000000545,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Who Builds It? A single entity (e.g., xAI, DARPA\nbut it cant be in the code itself, it needs to be lower, at assembly, preferably purely circuit logic, in the schematic for how to make robot brains, the cpu"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "33968050c298479dab6b1fb23292dfcf",
      "x": 47837.13198012043,
      "y": 25121.139009704355,
      "width": 311.2707034117775,
      "height": 428.6326636678059,
      "z_value": -9.468000000000295,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Within a value chain: don't optimize nodes that fail singleton-multiplier qualification\nWithin a cognitive framework: don't install reflexes on substrates that fail vacuum-recognition\nWithin a career: don't iterate skills on environments that don't permit precision saturation\nWithin a conversation: don't invest elaborate thought into a substrate that shows early interruption\nWithin an interaction with another person: don't pursue depth where stable repeatability isn't there to receive it\nAnd the unifying meta-principle running through all of them, which I think is the actual thing you live by and the actual reason the framework looks the way it does: commit only to substrates that can hold what you deposit into them. Everything else \u2014 the chain, the modular application, the risk weighting, the singleton multiplier, the reflex installation, the precision-over-speed inversion, the vacuum recognition \u2014 is just elaboration of that one principle applied at different layers and scales. The framework is the principle made operational. The reflex is the principle made automatic. The career trajectory is the principle made cumulative."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Market",
      "uuid": "62da15ce78774d46a2c5147797599e0d",
      "x": 8706.69999829951,
      "y": 6762.128798916687,
      "width": 329.95503634692204,
      "height": 152.0,
      "z_value": -9.94600000000003,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "He went to market one day and brought along his son\nTogether they purchased a Donkey.\nOn the way back he let the boy ride the Donkey\nAnd took a decision to walk alongside himself."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "bd923aa2e5c347c289dc34b195c543bf",
      "x": 37276.049277465514,
