    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Symptom B (ghost)",
      "uuid": "3fa81e2337f749ceaf67bc63d89b0e3f",
      "x": 86114.10033951806,
      "y": 23941.448208799015,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -9.165000000000463,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Shortly before the crash, a shake-deleted GitNode stayed rendered on the canvas for ~5 seconds after _prepare_for_removal complete logged cleanly, then vanished. No Python error, no Event Viewer entry \u2014 a pure repaint lag."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Pretty self explanatory if I would ask myself",
      "uuid": "df7d58b4f36e428386c9aecc66625edb",
      "x": 9149.237199585983,
      "y": 6648.235778264633,
      "width": 478.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.428000000000317,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Pretty self explanatory if I would ask myself",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Lesson learned",
      "uuid": "2213e60f687c4f87a2b36ab8af21f0f1",
      "x": 67415.30798898065,
      "y": 17620.66620448389,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -9.248000000000417,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Never use QTimer.singleShot to cross thread boundaries in PySide6. Use flags polled by a main-thread timer, or proper QMetaObject.invokeMethod with Qt.QueuedConnection."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "95aba154d007431696e3a47b6fd5cccc",
      "x": 39291.83699150231,
      "y": 5440.052280532,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 212.0,
      "z_value": -9.392000000000337,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1. __init__ starts a daemon thread running _render_worker()\n2. The worker calls _markdown_to_html(self.data.label) and stores the result in _pending_html\n3. A QTimer at 100ms interval polls _check_render_delivery() on the main thread\n4. When _pending_html is set, the timer stops, the HTML is injected into the QTextEdit"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
