    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "level 1 isn't even teachable in the conventional sense",
      "uuid": "613453f068ac489da791f66e7ab17b3b",
      "x": 47544.901071819775,
      "y": 23225.485786103774,
      "width": 582.0247957252577,
      "height": 169.42047975117748,
      "z_value": -9.475000000000291,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "It's a perceptual frame you either have or develop by being burned enough times by substrates\"\n  Same as any dancer, same as any musician, you can decide one day to become a musician, pick up a guitar and book a gig at a local pub, voila you are now a pro musician, but a pop idols training takes up to ten years sometimes just iterating again again again until she has mastered her skill before even starting the first show.  And that scales globally while the other is still at the pub 20 years later hoping one day someone notices them"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "All Glory",
      "uuid": "6dde773511c342ccafe6bbf43c35600f",
      "x": 2319.094348936987,
      "y": 4056.9374751778423,
      "width": 179.26073161367185,
      "height": 94.3898945152473,
      "z_value": -9.659000000000189,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Yeah, I'm here, what's up?"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "3cd60ba289fc42bf9a617f595d456fca",
      "x": 41737.56759032101,
      "y": 8537.928281459599,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.372000000000348,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "WarmNode body text gets a lighter pass (just  and  strip) so prose body keeps its in-line ISO dates and em-dashes verbatim."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "April 19th 2026: HealthNode post-teardow",
      "uuid": "a12ac24ed51248c185337a1633d8fdf9",
      "x": 90917.73905601593,
      "y": 27337.581503801634,
      "width": 707.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.137000000000478,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "April 19th 2026: HealthNode post-teardown timer fire on app shutdown",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "April 15th 2026: MarkdownNode",
      "uuid": "d6090685a4f942ba9a158a2238b1d9b3",
      "x": 55670.676140757656,
      "y": 13216.183105371703,
      "width": 318.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.298000000000389,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "April 15th 2026: MarkdownNode",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "21e2c838fc5c441a9244d85a449fb46a",
      "x": 42283.83516561045,
      "y": 17943.547390416905,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.519000000000267,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "And the corollary you implied but didn't state outright: the training has to be deterministic, not exploratory. Exploratory practice is for skill-building where the goal is adaptability. Reflex installation is the opposite \u2014 you're installing a fixed pattern that needs to fire identically every time, because the value of the reflex comes from its uniformity, not its flexibility. Flexibility is added later, on top, by the conscious layer that's now freed up to do higher-order work because the substrate is reliable. Determinism at the substrate is what permits adaptability at the surface."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "33c1549691de4a14b1677eaa7aec5182",
      "x": 90819.9018891997,
      "y": 27584.112828922545,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 422.0,
      "z_value": -9.138000000000478,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "- [ ] AST method count \u2014 python -c \"import ast; ...\" to confirm the class has the expected number of methods. Methods silently swallowed by a module-level function won't raise a syntax error.\n- [ ] Module-level function boundaries \u2014 any function at column 0 that appears mid-file will capture all subsequent indented code as nested functions. Verify nothing follows it at the wrong indent level.\n- [ ] \"Continued class\" comments \u2014 Python does not support resuming a class body. If you see # (continued) after a module-level def, the code below it is not in the class. Restructure immediately.\n- [ ] hasattr spot-check \u2014 for any method called in teardown paths (_prepare_for_removal, teardown, disconnect_all), verify with hasattr(ClassName, 'method_name') that it actually resolves at runtime.\n- [ ] crash.txt review \u2014 check logs/crash.txt after testing deletions. A ghost node (rendered but unclickable) is the telltale sign of a teardown exception that was swallowed by the deferred removal's try/except."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Phase 1 applicator",
      "uuid": "698cdd13a9494010abb9652af971fec4",
      "x": 30992.140707125607,
      "y": 7207.807904220638,
      "width": 283.0479687464176,
      "height": 95.76929248439865,
      "z_value": -9.60300000000022,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Completed with timing & prioritization layer"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Symptom",
      "uuid": "158b382f66684c4d9ababb4a6c701868",
      "x": 67024.54324784804,
      "y": 16882.913570001096,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.255000000000413,
