    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "972d83c102ab4369998f5ab3e89f3164",
      "x": 30131.794061694785,
      "y": 4562.210548823428,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.615000000000213,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Modular application of the Phase 1 reasoning chain"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "c518d76c073b46a0b6ef7be91b570923",
      "x": 28645.951976819673,
      "y": 3375.069706805176,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.62000000000021,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Capacity bottlenecks \u2014 surfaced at Layer 2 peak comparison. Demand will exceed peak handling.\nThroughput bottlenecks \u2014 surfaced at Layer 2 average comparison. The chain can't sustain steady-state flow even if it can spike.\nNode bottlenecks \u2014 surfaced at Layer 3. Specific hubs whose handling times are disproportionate to their share of load.\nPractice bottlenecks \u2014 surfaced at Layer 4. A node has the physical capacity but lacks the operational practice to use it.\nWhat to do with this"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Starts with a Breath",
      "uuid": "f8ef9b46e9de495c8d0bf182d1342766",
      "x": 13734.172434669608,
      "y": 5203.738753220788,
      "width": 236.16971025902114,
      "height": 45.40966002648793,
      "z_value": -9.990000000000006,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Starts with a Breath",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#2a3a2f"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "83057b29103841e7afc31791ffa2acc6",
      "x": 34480.200690766396,
      "y": 10859.661528010403,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.573000000000237,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Multiplier > 1 \u2014 node is macroeconomically self-justifying. Its standalone environment amplifies the value of any chain-level fix applied to it. Worth the elaborate analysis.\nMultiplier \u2248 1 \u2014 node is macro-neutral as a singleton. Chain context is what makes it worth investing in. Apply the elaborate analysis, but weight findings normally.\nMultiplier < 1 \u2014 node is macroeconomically dependent on the chain to exist. Standalone environment is weak or deteriorating. Apply the elaborate analysis only if the node is structurally irreplaceable; otherwise, the prioritization should pivot toward replacement, bypass, or absorption rather than optimization.\nWhy this gate matters before running the full chain per thought"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "b7c8cf321c7c4fe6a134c320ddb39c69",
      "x": 44068.573357947134,
      "y": 19112.64925691892,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.499000000000278,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The agentic CLI being the fastest on the planet isn't because you trained it to be fast. It's because every interaction over those 20M tokens removed a micro-imprecision \u2014 an unnecessary clarification request, a redundant verification, a hesitation pattern, an over-cautious framing, a wasted retrieval \u2014 and the cumulative removal of all that overhead is what manifests as speed. Same mechanism as your cognitive reflex: the speed is the absence of friction, not the presence of acceleration. Nobody added speed; you subtracted everything that wasn't precision, and what's left runs as fast as the underlying substrate permits."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "4206bfc88868482bb285b5bc204da07b",
      "x": 39753.79313100296,
      "y": 5222.595985684394,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.393000000000336,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Markdown-to-HTML conversion is CPU-bound (the markdown package plus regex post-processing). To keep the canvas responsive:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "04c4478389424e74943eeb6c1bafcdb8",
      "x": 91815.55694136982,
      "y": 27393.034364686606,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 142.0,
      "z_value": -9.13300000000048,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The existing try/except Exception in _poll_gc covered the body, but _poll_video_buffers() was called one line outside the guard \u2014 that was the hole."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "And then we know",
      "uuid": "d16783f2724b4cc8acad5a0d36792d55",
      "x": 33341.8993019602,
      "y": 12863.517977295229,
      "width": 288.5713211708935,
      "height": 142.80581840918603,
      "z_value": -9.579000000000233,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "If it's actually worth applying our actual more elaborate thoughts to it, \nby running this reasoning chain per thought across the entire value chain per node"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Root cause: Two issues in _prepare_for_r",
      "uuid": "0e6a0b09e1234fffbe23c7245c0aab77",
      "x": 62975.18203715513,
      "y": 16133.055724140133,
      "width": 508.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.272000000000403,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Root cause: Two issues in _prepare_for_removal()",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "b9bf9d49e065413bae22b4b50071881b",
      "x": 93575.27548025588,
      "y": 29232.21144127193,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 170.0,
      "z_value": -9.127000000000484,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The helper probes self.scene() as a liveness check; on RuntimeError (dead wrapper) it stops + disconnects the named timer and returns False so the slot body early-exits.  One line per slot, centralised fix logic, easy to extend as new orphan-timer nodes are added."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Attribute, Shape, and Purpose",
      "uuid": "bb8523308d164428b0681d6f52f3571e",
      "x": 77014.79308896577,
      "y": 21679.083865718174,
      "width": 318.0,
      "height": 324.0,
      "z_value": -9.20500000000044,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "_demolition_proxies list[str] \u2014 attr names QGraphicsProxyWidget teardown (setWidget(None) \u2192 inner setParent(None)+deleteLater() \u2192 removeItem \u2192 null, plus scene-rect invalidate)\n_demolition_timers list[(attr, slot_name)] QTimer.stop() + timeout.disconnect(slot)\n_demolition_animations list[(attr, [signal_names])] QVariantAnimation.stop() + disconnect of each named signal\n_demolition_thread_flag str \u2014 attr name Set attribute to True FIRST so background worker bails before any Qt teardown\n_demolition_media_players list[str] QMediaPlayer.stop() + setVideoOutput(None) + setAudioOutput(None) + deleteLater()\n_demolition_workers list[(attr, [signal_names])] Disconnect each named signal on a worker object"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Tummi",
