      "z_value": -9.574000000000236,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Each node receives a singleton economic rating \u2014 a multiplier applied to the gain/effort/risk output of the rest of the Phase 1 chain. Conceptually:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "1. Scene-level quiescence counter",
      "uuid": "9cc8dc224c59486885ee9fdfeee6019e",
      "x": 69767.44750709801,
      "y": 17846.604832585275,
      "width": 359.0,
      "height": 184.0,
      "z_value": -9.240000000000421,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "(nodes/BaseNode.py::_shake_delete_group).\nA counter on the scene (scene._bulk_removing) is raised before the deferred-removal loop and lowered two event-loop ticks after the last QTimer.singleShot(0, removeItem) \u2014 the double-defer guarantees that any repaint scheduled by those removals still sees the flag raised. A counter (not a boolean) composes safely across overlapping bursts."
    },
    {
