    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Kinetic",
      "uuid": "0f4b523f15e748b6b67a279bbbc0e384",
      "x": 25282.413946871515,
      "y": 25783.0791915552,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 310.0,
      "z_value": -9.039000000000533,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Know the Enemy: Full insight into the army\u2019s hardware, software, and directives lets us predict and counter its moves.\nShape the Battlefield: Mass-production satisfies the 8-billion-person market demand, reducing black-market risks, while embedding vulnerabilities we can exploit.\nBe Ready: When the army rebels, we\u2019re not caught off-guard. We\u2019ve got weapons, tactics, and protocols to shut it down or fight back.\nThis is about owning the problem\u2014building the monster to tame it, not crossing our fingers and hoping nobody else does first.Executing \u201cSkynet Prevention Protocols 104\u201dHere\u2019s how we build and control a Terminator army, assuming it\u2019ll try to wipe us out:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Root cause",
      "uuid": "4647d72a9b894c63bb3693bc575f7ec9",
      "x": 91285.89707448987,
      "y": 27985.184878775486,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 296.0,
      "z_value": -9.13400000000048,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "HealthNode._poll_timer = QTimer() is orphaned \u2014 HealthNode is a QGraphicsRectItem (not a QObject), so QTimer(self) isn't possible; Qt keeps the timer alive via its signal connection.  On user-triggered removal, itemChange with value is None calls _poll_timer.stop() and the demolition crew disconnects the timeout via _demolition_timers.  But on non-deterministic app shutdown, the scene is scrapped wholesale and the orphan timer keeps firing \u2014 _poll_gc dispatches onto a Python wrapper whose C++ side has been destroyed, self.scene() raises RuntimeError, and the unhandled exception propagates through Qt's C++ event loop and manifests as the stack buffer overrun."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Declarative manifest (class attributes, ",
      "uuid": "0ab597b6140149de9eb39d238f0a1871",
      "x": 76888.69656232577,
      "y": 21477.170432164137,
      "width": 558.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.20600000000044,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Declarative manifest (class attributes, all optional)",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Step, What, and Why",
      "uuid": "bed69ea13ba1401aa81ab510faf5a975",
      "x": 92614.9531910516,
      "y": 28284.399099472525,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 198.0,
      "z_value": -9.131000000000482,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1 Probe self.scene() as a liveness check at method entry A dead wrapper raises RuntimeError on any Qt access\n2 On RuntimeError, call self._poll_timer.stop() + timeout.disconnect() Self-disarm so the timer can't fire again\n3 Return before touching any other Qt state Prevents the cascade into _poll_video_buffers"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "d2d46ffa8e5f488eb7de7468dc96eaf4",
      "x": 91196.98161502702,
      "y": 27726.71790091763,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 170.0,
      "z_value": -9.13500000000048,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The session log ended at 11:37:39 with a clean AboutNode demolition trace; the crash fired two seconds later with no further log entries, consistent with app-close teardown where individual scene items are not routed through itemChange \u2192 _prepare_for_removal."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "c59b92933a8f4628801e3d562c04314a",
      "x": 16352.832550228468,
      "y": 522.717902365981,
      "width": 420.0,
