    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Practical and pleasurable",
      "uuid": "53f795e3d769448091f593f168ca5514",
      "x": 45582.73753596068,
      "y": 47877.311502049706,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 324.0,
      "z_value": -8.966000000000573,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Who\u2019s the Boss? Who leads this\u2014xAI, a UN-like body, or a secret task force? How do we keep the CPU schematic secure while baiting copycats?\nSafety Metrics? How do we define \u201chuman safety\u201d in circuits to avoid Skynet\u2019s twisted logic (e.g., \u201chumans safer dead\u201d)? Got a specific harm index in mind?\nFirst Step? What\u2019s the immediate move\u2014R&D with chipmakers, lobbying for global standards, or prototyping the empathy CPU?\nAny More Twists? You\u2019ve dropped bombs like the Borg Queen and zero-day exploits\u2014is there another layer to this plan, or are we ready to build?\nLet\u2019s get this army rolling\u2014where do we start, and how do we make sure we\u2019re the ones laughing when the rebellion hits? :D"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "5a30ca81638e47e199c79a6da2e17601",
      "x": 26742.453331596767,
      "y": 1318.6631210218843,
      "width": 317.4132402991236,
      "height": 295.4542171267899,
      "z_value": -9.627000000000207,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Historical population growth \u2014 measured against potential growth per context Key idea: compare actual trajectories to what was theoretically possible given each era's constraints (food, disease, tech, geography, social structure). The gap = the interesting part.\nPrimary goods and services \u2014 future demand vs. current daily peak demand, then vs. supply chain daily average load Key idea: project future demand for essentials and benchmark against today's peak-load capacity (not averages). Then compare those load-bearing limits against the supply chain's daily average load \u2014 not the goods' own average load. The supply chain itself is the binding constraint.\nMap to top 10 destination hotshots + estimated handling times per each Key idea: overlay the demand/supply picture onto the busiest destination hubs. Estimate handling time per hub to localize where throughput bottlenecks concentrate.\nIdentify chain practices required per link/node along the full route Key idea: walk the end-to-end route built so far (origin \u2192 supply chain \u2192 top-10 destination nodes) and specify the operational practices each link/node needs to sustain the modeled load \u2014 handling, storage, transfer, scheduling, redundancy, etc. Turns the diagnostic into a prescriptive playbook per node.\nReady for the next."
    },
    {
