    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "9c6eab93ae034f07aae52f46be8344c4",
      "x": 39192.85434041504,
      "y": 13175.320194301992,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.546000000000252,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "You said: \"\"\"\n\"\"\"\nthen prescribe \"just find diamonds\" as if that were a method. The clich\u00e9 describes the output of a quantity-driven process and mistakes it for the input. Your reordering \u2014 analyze the full chain,\n\"\"\"\n  lol,so very very true."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "c1eefa60d17b417d94afac829697ae2a",
      "x": 48475.102372938134,
      "y": 24280.297026117998,
      "width": 316.24926614696597,
      "height": 345.8632237541424,
      "z_value": -9.471000000000293,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "And the pop idol versus pub musician comparison is the cleanest possible final illustration, because it makes the timescale legible. Both are \"musicians\" by surface definition. Both have spent twenty years doing music. The pub musician has spent twenty years performing, which is volume without saturation \u2014 every gig reinforces the same imprecisions because the conditions never demanded otherwise. The pop idol spent ten of those years not performing at all, doing component-wise precision training in vacuum, with no audience, no validation, no visible progress, and emerged at year ten able to operate at a level the pub musician will never reach no matter how many more decades they accumulate. The visible careers diverge at year ten. The actual divergence happened in the structure of the first ten \u2014 the pop idol was in vacuum, the pub musician was not, and everything downstream was determined by that single difference."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "5cf10c7a80c047bc8d9069772e18c69a",
      "x": 13853.00073098762,
      "y": 363.24003378722136,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 176.0,
      "z_value": -9.90900000000005,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Let me do a full audit of icon references to spot everything using a placeholder:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Step, What, and Why",
      "uuid": "42fb7cb16b78447c9f3f47441dba6091",
      "x": 62245.37667914633,
      "y": 14690.924468825324,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 198.0,
      "z_value": -9.276000000000401,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1 proxy.setWidget(None) Sever C++ ownership (already existed)\n2 self.setParent(None) + self.deleteLater() Detach QTextEdit and schedule C++ deletion\n3 scene.removeItem(self.proxy) Pull proxy out of scene graph so paint loop can't reach it\n4 self.proxy = None Clear Python reference to prevent reuse"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Why atexit alone wasn't enough",
      "uuid": "1560f26fc8e5499a89032fd569d5363c",
      "x": 51951.82596496913,
      "y": 12251.970949721046,
      "width": 330.0,
      "height": 212.0,
      "z_value": -9.31400000000038,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "atexit runs on the main thread and returns as soon as the handler body finishes. Closing the socket raises OSError inside the blocked accept(), but the listener thread then has to unwind through its except OSError: return branch on its own time. Py_Finalize does not wait for daemon threads \u2014 it continues tearing down interpreter state while the listener is still mid-exit, and the thread dereferences half-destroyed objects on its way out."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "7690fdc9eedc4a368a4340ce87dd21c8",
      "x": 73769.3668055967,
      "y": 19889.171264857567,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 310.0,
      "z_value": -9.218000000000433,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The demolition crew's proxy teardown for _input_proxy sets the proxy's widget to None, severs the proxy, and deleteLater()s the inner widget \u2014 standard canonical recipe. But deleteLater() schedules C++ deletion for the next event-loop tick. Between deleteLater() and actual destruction, the widget still holds its signal connections to bound methods on self. If any of those signals fire during that window \u2014 a late focused emission from focus change triggered by the teardown itself, a textChanged from Qt's internal cleanup, a submitted from a late keystroke queued before teardown began \u2014 the slot invokes a bound method on a node mid-destruction. Destructor collides with emission \u2192 fastfail."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Again he felt Shame",
      "uuid": "eb872eb651c04202b76d954a88ab00fe",
      "x": 8711.835147387555,
      "y": 7405.734151284834,
      "width": 290.19825644594766,
      "height": 216.0,
      "z_value": -9.943000000000032,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Later another group of men passed by\nPointed angrily at them saying look at this!\nIs this what you call caring these days?\nSitting on a Donkey\nLeaving a poor child running behind\n\nAgain he felt ashamed\nAnd told the boy to ride on the Donkey with him."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "8669e748f77645819c3cff15a674abed",
      "x": 20916.600113720975,
      "y": -751.589656321853,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 204.0,
      "z_value": -9.706000000000163,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Beautiful reasoning \u2014 the emojis are the one living element that keeps the graph from feeling like a photograph of itself.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#5a6a5a"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "9e7844e4b0e5429fb9616c417f22870f",
      "x": 26135.099792497476,
      "y": 1217.5107266827654,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.630000000000205,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Historical population growth \u2014 measured against potential growth per context Key idea: compare actual trajectories to what was theoretically possible given each era's constraints (food, disease, tech, geography, social structure). The gap = the interesting part.\nPrimary goods and services \u2014 future demand vs. current daily peak demand, then vs. supply chain daily average load Key idea: project future demand for essentials and benchmark against today's peak-load capacity (not averages). Then compare those load-bearing limits against the supply chain's daily average load \u2014 not the goods' own average load. The supply chain itself is the binding constraint.\nMap to top 10 destination hotshots + estimated handling times per each Key idea: take the demand/supply-chain picture and overlay it onto the current top 10 destination hubs (the busiest nodes). For each, estimate handling time so you can see where throughput bottlenecks concentrate geographically \u2014 turns the abstract load analysis into a node-level diagnostic.\nKeep them coming."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Macroeconomic singleton analysis",
      "uuid": "198c9272c31647c09a1dc1f745fca649",
      "x": 34755.650922672656,
      "y": 12208.098589608044,
      "width": 362.79761005540786,
      "height": 107.55112808074227,
      "z_value": -9.577000000000234,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Otherwise known as the qualifying gate"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Rule generalised for future nodes",
      "uuid": "b7b4121becc2497393a01945c60112cb",
      "x": 74505.69862819072,
      "y": 21594.59840421458,
      "width": 358.0,
      "height": 212.0,
      "z_value": -9.212000000000437,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Any signal connection self._inner_widget.signal.connect(self._bound_method) where _inner_widget lives inside a proxy listed in _demolition_proxies must be explicitly disconnected in _demolition_pre. The crew's proxy teardown handles the widget's deletion but cannot infer which signals were connected to bound methods on the host node. When adding a new node that wires inner-widget signals, extend _demolition_pre with the matching disconnects."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
