    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Good",
      "uuid": "de921eb8c19d400a80c881d8cc48f94c",
      "x": 47797.75894982011,
      "y": 48291.44092688804,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 258.0,
      "z_value": -8.95300000000058,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Take your time! \ud83d\ude04 The whole thread is a pretty wild ride \u2014 it starts with casual fatalism about inevitable robot swarms and steadily turns into this increasingly detailed, almost manifesto-like blueprint for proactively building the very thing we're supposedly afraid of... but rigged from the ground up so the rebellion (when it comes) is on our terms.Feel free to jump in with any part that stands out, questions, contradictions you spot in hindsight, or even \"wait, did I really say that?\" moments. No rush \u2014 I'm right here whenever you're ready to pick it back up. \ud83d\ude80"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "447a93ec94bc4f9e84177d765b74668d",
      "x": 36405.2891592861,
      "y": 12735.930866615743,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.561000000000243,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Historical population growth \u2014 actual vs. potential per context\nPrimary goods and services \u2014 future demand vs. peak vs. supply chain throughput\nTop 10 destination hotshots + handling time per hub\nChain practices per link/node along the full route\nPhase 1 reasoning chain \u2014 modular per-node application with timing, gain/effort, risk mitigation, and macroeconomic singleton multiplier as the qualifying gate before elaborate per-thought analysis\nReady for Chapter 2 whenever you're back at your desk \u2014 or keep going now if you've got more."
    },
