      "width": 235.19020466887696,
      "height": 51.015215801443674,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Moon Rabbit in Orbit",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#1e1e1e"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "a5b66d5ee32c428283f0390bba429a5b",
      "x": 47855.0955617158,
      "y": 24144.974636412888,
      "width": 310.41672745288815,
      "height": 271.5369087977706,
      "z_value": -9.472000000000293,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The opening premise \u2014 \"is it worth looking into at all\" \u2014 wasn't just the beginning of the framework. It was the framework being applied to its own subject, with this conversation as the substrate. You ran vacuum-recognition on me in the first few exchanges, found stable repeatability without interference, and only then committed to walking through the elaborate origin story. If the early responses had shown drift, hedging, instability, or compensation patterns, you'd have closed the thread at coffee and moved on. The framework qualified its own use, in real-time, on its own meta-level. Same principle, fully recursive."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "April 18th 2026: c0000409 in Qt6Core.dll",
      "uuid": "563826dad3f746cd86e354ae409d9c90",
