    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Symptom",
      "uuid": "48cba04dc17e49ed98fe902a96ab960b",
      "x": 98021.20864805444,
      "y": 31243.1782190889,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 170.0,
      "z_value": -9.112000000000492,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Session switch while a prior session held an AudioNode (not playing) and the incoming session had two VideoNodes mid-loop-with-audio. App tore the old session down, then crashed. Event Viewer: access violation 0xc0000005 in Qt6Core.dll. crash.txt carried the unraisable:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Why per-node _prepare_for_removal doesn't prevent this",
      "uuid": "4c09a0d485304e0e9fde9fc291b2b7ed",
      "x": 72655.72636055456,
      "y": 18417.661183713444,
      "width": 569.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.229000000000427,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "_prepare_for_removal is correct and cleans up properly \u2014 but it only runs during removeItem, not before it. The race lives in the window between split-returning and removeItem-dispatching, during which _prepare_for_removal hasn't run yet."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Root cause",
      "uuid": "beaff9e23a70431ca59a2e1fd7bddab1",
      "x": 67390.1170393015,
      "y": 16869.592885642793,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -9.254000000000413,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "QTimer.singleShot(0, callback) from worker threads doesn't reliably queue into the main thread's event loop in PySide6. The per-future _kick_refresh and final _on_push_done callbacks were silently dropped."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "4536ceb8db9742a0ac3bf94cffe9b661",
      "x": 51795.56238345613,
      "y": 28157.6770049036,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.439000000000311,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Anyway \u2014 that's a lot of dense thread for a coffee-and-travel-prep window, and I think we genuinely landed it. The opening premise (is this worth looking into) ran recursively through the whole conversation, qualified itself, ignited briefly, deposited what it was supposed to deposit, and is now winding back down to substrate. Which is exactly the pulse shape we just spent an hour describing. The conversation itself obeyed the principle. Couldn't have scripted that better."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "bb9e95f450fc49bca12983960904c99e",
      "x": 34336.35789535301,
      "y": 11734.232205708697,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.572000000000237,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Without the singleton qualifier, every node gets equal analytical investment, and the elaborate reasoning chain gets spent on nodes that are economically marginal regardless of how well-optimized their chain participation becomes. The multiplier acts as a triage filter: it tells you which nodes deserve the full per-thought walkthrough, and which ones should be evaluated for structural replacement instead of optimization. It also reframes \"fixing\" \u2014 sometimes the highest-leverage move on a low-multiplier node isn't to optimize it, it's to redesign around it."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "The vacuum is the precondition, everything else is consequence",
      "uuid": "ce9198a7419f43e7891519ef560f1184",
