      "title": "Text",
      "uuid": "6933afb06c324c0991bd2950c5280572",
      "x": 21532.20741138601,
      "y": 4619.024925363211,
      "width": 260.0224848672117,
      "height": 241.5805038783251,
      "z_value": -9.950000000000028,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "This works quite fine\nSure some people would just\nAdd a font selector to a node\n\nBut we went ahead \nAnd created a text node\nFor the Lato font writing \nAnd an About node \nFor the chandler42 writing,\n\nNo no sir we no be clicking and licking\nThings we are not supposed to.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "",
      "render_html": false
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "9d977941b5634693966b5020a9d91bf9",
      "x": 30043.405921504364,
      "y": 7033.448816235417,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.607000000000218,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "This reframes the work: Phase 1 layered = diagnose the system. Phase 1 modular = characterize the components so Phase 2 can engineer the joints."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Label normalisation",
      "uuid": "42ebb10cbf2749c38c64d4f38f2d0e58",
      "x": 41142.739932507524,
      "y": 8343.545169794528,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 114.0,
      "z_value": -9.374000000000347,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "All AboutNode labels and WarmNode titles run through prettify_label() (in utils/label_cleanup.py):"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "markdown package",
      "uuid": "f97137eec7dc4df8bd556a05730eadbb",
      "x": 38741.53503786602,
      "y": 6329.570923638159,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 170.0,
      "z_value": -9.38800000000034,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "converts raw markdown to HTML using three extensions:\n   - tables \u2014 pipe-delimited table syntax\n   - fenced_code \u2014 triple-backtick code blocks\n   - codehilite \u2014 syntax highlighting via Pygments (Monokai theme, inline styles)"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "df641d20f1cc40a6ab994517ae749388",
      "x": 72656.77717584236,
      "y": 18025.438630566627,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 296.0,
      "z_value": -9.230000000000427,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "- Qt6Core.dll (not Widgets) points to QObject / signal-slot / QTimer machinery, not paint.\n- c0000409 fastfail fires when Qt's C++ destructor begins disconnect()'ing signals while an emission is still in flight targeting the same object.\n- MarkdownNode has live QObject machinery \u2014 a 100 ms _delivery_timer firing into _check_render_delivery, plus a background render thread \u2014 that keeps running between the synchronous _split_into_nodes() and the deferred scene.removeItem(node).\n- When the 100ms timer fires into the soon-to-die node at the same event-loop tick the deferred removeItem dispatches, the QObject destructor and the signal emission collide \u2192 fastfail."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "c744d3668cd74713b03af83ac2bcc9b2",
      "x": 24717.791022805523,
      "y": -2480.044618651191,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.645000000000197,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Historical population growth \u2014 (awaiting your take)\nWhat's your angle on it? Long-term trends, a specific era, drivers (agriculture, industrialization, medicine), or something else?"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "7e0ab295c81a4766b1f3e635ef6d02b5",
      "x": 25161.0849460305,
      "y": -45.130169723751806,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.633000000000203,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Historical population growth \u2014 measured against potential growth per context Key idea: compare actual trajectories to what was theoretically possible given each era's constraints (food, disease, tech, geography, social structure). The gap = the interesting part.\nPrimary goods and services \u2014 future demand vs. current daily peak demand, then vs. supply chain daily average load Key idea: project future demand for essentials and benchmark against today's peak-load capacity (not averages). Then compare those load-bearing limits against the supply chain's daily average load \u2014 not the goods' own average load. The supply chain itself is the binding constraint, and its steady-state throughput is what determines whether peaks can actually be met.\nReady for the next one whenever."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Ambiguity of Language",
      "uuid": "91b68d654eaf4bf589380058879bdf07",
      "x": 3070.0606869088865,
      "y": 5299.560415208134,
      "width": 371.5650196633692,
      "height": 143.84144653124622,
      "z_value": -9.419000000000322,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Words like \"burned,\" \"library,\" and \"sunshine\" \nThey all have multiple senses \nLiteral, metaphorical, and symbolic\nAllowing each component to branch into different meanings."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "New Thought",
      "uuid": "64e1a1ee55f745f2a5a6ac9b44d82544",
      "x": 48149.83995630597,
      "y": 48689.11562960032,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 198.0,
      "z_value": -8.95200000000058,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "what would you suggest given current abilities would be the best way to grab a copy of this entire thread for more further detailed reading to the side? I usually just blatantly select and copy paste the text into a notepad for a second copy, can you provide the whole conversation in a single copy/paste markdown frame or would you suggest some other form of export?"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Root cause",
      "uuid": "69d0d9d5deb4410981ec643709c2d56b",
      "x": 65252.937975506866,
      "y": 16133.629921370259,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -9.262000000000409,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "QTimer.singleShot(0, _remove) left the VideoNode in the scene between hide and removal \u2014 the player could deliver a frame to the dead sink. Glide timers on wires were stopped but not disconnected."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Boundless Joy",
      "uuid": "d265e421f9ba4c77b2717a76b3517b33",
      "x": 50103.03686004944,
      "y": -5231.536457280597,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -8.907000000000606,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Read 2 files\nRead both supporting files too \u2014 text_chunker and label_cleanup are the introspection arsenal. Here's what I see when I lay the three split philosophies side by side."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "f885bf31deac45dab55300dfc7b5a2a6",
      "x": 44460.38116993274,
      "y": 10083.886760589538,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 172.0,
      "z_value": -9.348000000000361,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Both MarkdownNode and TextNode contain identical copies of _cozy_tree_line(). This is a local function inside _markdown_to_html() / the equivalent in TextNode. It converts ASCII tree lines (the \u251c\u2500\u2500 \ud83d\udcc1 folder/ format) into styled HTML spans."
    },
