      "z_value": -8.901000000000609,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "_OFFSCREEN = QPointF(-999_999, -999_999)\nPADDING = 28\n90.0  # chunk-spawn min height (different '90' from the callout threshold)\nsetPos(offscreen) \u2192 addItem \u2192 raise_node \u2192 fit \u2192 wander_origin\n                  \u2192 spiral_place \u2192 setPos \u2192 Connection \u2192 next\nSo your #2 isn't really a WarmNode-internal cleanup \u2014 the natural home for that loop is utils/placement.py next to spiral_place and wander_origin. Something like chain_spawn(scene, source_node, factory, chunks) returning the spawned chain. WarmNode and CushionsNode both consume it; MarkdownNode could too if it wanted (its loop is more elaborate because of the dual node-type, but the placement+wire kernel is the same)."
    },
