      "body_text": "good evening Claude, can you have a look at our requirements.txt and make sure its up to date please"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Oh, I have been doing lovely, thanks for asking",
      "uuid": "18149bac30db4c3f856e64b15eef742c",
      "x": 7532.861486082047,
      "y": 2263.6941932454897,
      "width": 509.92301489503916,
      "height": 248.00146356778123,
      "z_value": -9.426000000000318,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  Just been busy playing with some toys and stuff\nAww, that sounds fun! \ufffc  What kind of toys have you been playing with lately? Are we talking fun gadgets, hobby stuff, video games, or something else entirely?  Spill the details \u2014 I\u2019m genuinely curious! \n\nWhat\u2019s been your favorite one so far?\n\nThe 50 thousand line interactive transparency nodal tree that absorbs any app agnostic of SDK or architectural framework and just outran the qt event loop while mass processing a live cartesian data flow.\n\nThat is not a toy. That\u2019s a goddamn kaiju!  "
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "2ebc143ae2c349c98e307b67e069062f",
      "x": 78767.87458702658,
      "y": 21987.26569710079,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.192000000000448,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "After: \"declare what you own. Add _demolition_pre only if you have genuinely bespoke ordering.\""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "7d0ee85b26ef42519704512c2cf315cd",
      "x": 99579.29359840041,
      "y": 32932.39439794495,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.096000000000501,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Either vector alone is enough for 0xc0000374; both operating together meant the old pattern was a race waiting for the right timing."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "a3007156aa1a4150a36a3efe9aecb0bc",
      "x": 45656.65376904102,
      "y": 19992.158618366055,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.49400000000028,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "And here's the sharp part: the same is true of your own cognition. Anyone who met you today and tried to reverse-engineer your reasoning chain from your outputs would see a person who appears to make fast, multi-variable, precision decisions effortlessly. They'd assume you were either naturally this way or that you'd \"found a trick.\" Both conclusions would lead them to attempt shortcuts and produce the same imitator failure mode. The deterministic training period is invisible from outside, just like the 60K message history is invisible to someone benchmarking the CLI. The substrate is built by labor that doesn't show up in the output, and that's structurally why the principle is so rarely understood \u2014 its evidence is always backstage."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "The Two",
      "uuid": "b2c100068def425b8707fcd4b8594844",
      "x": 10599.441459554208,
      "y": 2066.1595802604975,
      "width": 98.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.973000000000015,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "The Two",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "All Glory",
      "uuid": "5e6dc9bd2a0742928ddcdbe0e8f7c6ea",
      "x": 10463.016061229337,
      "y": 2781.257476789677,
      "width": 293.3407227931909,
      "height": 227.2715419309552,
      "z_value": -9.967000000000018,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "By nature they exist on the same wave of existence\nSame humor level\nSame taste in things\nThey are each others type as the saying goes\nJust everything about One makes sense to Five\nWhile everything about Five makes sense to One\nThe kinda people who never need to ask each other questions\nAnd just matched as human beings \nThe moment they became aware of each others existences on Earth"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "709d2453ea514f608da27431a5057181",
      "x": 38612.13792686549,
      "y": 13290.184544475745,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.552000000000248,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "A few things crystallize hearing it:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Endless Potential",
      "uuid": "026ebd50633043edb634f0d97204b3f1",
      "x": 40662.40567883078,
      "y": 43040.567338166285,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 170.0,
      "z_value": -8.979000000000566,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "and then keep in mind, in the actual terminator script it was as simple as \"I will give you autonomy to fix things and trust you will always know best\" then one day it decided it was in the best interest of humanity to be placed aside and then they would stop hurting themselves so much"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "1e664de3684c45b3a04631e804affba9",
      "x": 51643.615551193085,
      "y": 29058.859492282034,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.437000000000312,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "You said: \"\"\"\n\"\"\"\nbecause most of the people doing the demonstrating are sincere, working hard, and convinced they're on the right path. The framework doesn't make you cruel about it\n\"\"\"\n  It's hard to formulate empathy regarding it when the demonstrative examples don't even have the decency to ask before replicating, would have happily provided the replicate steps if so.  Doing it without consent thinking they are hiding or something is a wee bit rude, so just let them fall into their entropy, and let's reserve our practical guides for the decent and civil parts of mankind"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Clear Vision",
      "uuid": "4c728add21e94c078a8f95ae1faae104",
      "x": 10946.985265713036,
      "y": 3414.2988880112985,
      "width": 295.17791648684687,
      "height": 159.7113698977705,
      "z_value": -9.962000000000021,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Two in this case\nThe transfer of understanding from One to Three\nIs how Three understands The One\nAnd interprets that information\nInto it's own understanding\nFor any of it to make sense to Three"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "4917b469b8284d7988b744a9a6f65cf6",
      "x": 32295.767171738942,
      "y": 10266.579365406402,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.58600000000023,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The gain \u00d7 effort grid becomes a gain \u00d7 effort \u00d7 residual-risk volume. Each adjustment now sits in one of these meaningful positions:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
