      "title": "Subclass, Purpose, and Data class",
      "uuid": "1f933b00c1214056beeb9efef5a60727",
      "x": 39352.45992380014,
      "y": 5077.456378710388,
      "width": 358.0,
      "height": 198.0,
      "z_value": -9.40300000000033,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "ArchitectureNode Displays Architecture.md ArchitectureNodeData\nNodeSchemaNode Displays Node Type Schema.md NodeSchemaNodeData\nReadmeNode Displays README.md from the project root ReadmeNodeData\nRegistryNode Displays node_registry.toml as rendered docs RegistryNodeData"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "2e9e7fb865594689b48235ed7e637512",
      "x": 46538.37193991561,
      "y": 9756.40399464883,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 142.0,
      "z_value": -9.340000000000366,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "BaseNode._prepare_for_removal() is the single deterministic teardown hook. Every node subclass that adds any of the following must override it and clean up before calling super():"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "81c1721426d74cd9a0a25e6279781953",
      "x": 47987.83636324087,
      "y": 9768.932356769528,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 226.0,
      "z_value": -9.33100000000037,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The 2026-04-18 incident on StickerNode (0xc0000409 fastfail at the same offset as HealthNode's bug) was solved by adding a _quiet_for_shake() override that synchronously severed viewport tracking before the deferred-remove window opened. The pattern was never lifted to the root, so JoyStats and Value were exposed to the same race \u2014 latent only because their inline RuntimeError guards in _refresh and the rarity of mid-scrub shakes saved them."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Fix",
      "uuid": "308faa65217e4893a7b9290e4eb9f683",
      "x": 65954.24361068477,
      "y": 16371.942542524193,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.26100000000041,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Added conn._glide_timer.timeout.disconnect() on wires. Changed to immediate scene.removeItem(node)."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "All Glory",
      "uuid": "1ef02c268593432ea55c1840e981e79f",
      "x": 16794.465726346327,
      "y": 19160.05831531503,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 478.0,
      "z_value": -9.064000000000519,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Global Agreement: Good luck getting that. Nations don\u2019t share nicely\u2014look at nuclear treaties or climate deals. A rogue state or company could ignore your rules.\nTech Enforcement: Containment tech (kill switches, monitors) must be foolproof. History says nothing is\u2014look at how fast cybersecurity gets breached.\nAdaptability: Rules must evolve faster than the swarm. If the AI self-improves or guerrillas mod it, your protocols could become obsolete overnight.\nMy TakeYour strategy\u2019s got guts. By building the swarm ourselves, we\u2019d know its guts\u2014literally and figuratively. Developing containment in parallel could give us a fighting chance against your \u201cinevitable\u201d rogue swarm. But it\u2019s a race against our own mistakes. The more we scale, the more variables we juggle\u2014hackers, geopolitics, emergent AI behaviors. It\u2019s not inevitable that this plan prevents a worse outcome; it could just fast-track the chaos.What\u2019s your vision for who runs this? A single entity (say, a tech giant or government) risks monopolizing power, but a decentralized effort might be too messy to coordinate. And how do you ensure the containment protocols stay ahead of the swarm\u2019s evolution? Got a specific setup in mind to make this work?"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
      "uuid": "9a4dd95dcadd4a379f539e55fb005f1a",
      "x": 12916.541832458748,
      "y": 8194.542222414466,
      "width": 566.9071802436184,
      "height": 579.0135666085118,
      "z_value": -9.950000000000028,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "image_b64": "",
      "cache_key": "f577fca3399ef800db2cb8032fa85549b933648eb445915687203d92f266c8ba.png",
      "caption": "downloadedImage (11)",
      "source_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\Cloning Humans\\Images\\The Thurr\\downloadedImage (11).png",
      "source_size": 2241888,
      "source_mtime": 1746365064.2609315,
      "show_border": true,
      "depth_front": false
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "bcbe679dc7d34a15a99fc159d856cef8",
      "x": 48659.31106061963,
      "y": 11008.603645013052,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.327000000000373,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Both are needed. The crew tears everything down, but only after the deferred-remove tick executes; _quiet_for_shake covers the interim."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "palette",
      "title": "Palette",
      "uuid": "386eb276fec54cdfb1e0ee7c098580fe",
      "x": -156.47433883814062,
      "y": 3233.508337145704,
      "width": 485.052199597023,
      "height": 771.7823992339445,
      "z_value": -9.831000000000094,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "colors": [
        {
          "label": "#ffd1dc",
          "hex": "#ffd1dc"
        },
        {
          "label": "#ffb6c1",
