      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Guard: _removal_done",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Fix applied to nodes/HealthNode.py::_pol",
      "uuid": "aa74a8b0858442e49e63a47639db6a73",
      "x": 92199.53828169052,
      "y": 27551.454679688897,
      "width": 468.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.132000000000481,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Fix applied to nodes/HealthNode.py::_poll_gc",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Symptom",
      "uuid": "8ac6d5d3d7d44c2c97db003facdc4f7a",
      "x": 56052.37660389148,
      "y": 12933.910820294874,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.29700000000039,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Access violation in Qt6Widgets.dll on app close. Event Viewer showed exception 0xc0000005 in the Qt paint loop."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Step, What, and Why",
      "uuid": "2353e626ac684f5fbedc8d4f8b4b448c",
      "x": 57729.880234369106,
      "y": 13055.750737676586,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 282.0,
      "z_value": -9.292000000000392,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1 Added self._removed = False flag in __init__ Coordination signal between threads\n2 Set self._removed = True at top of _prepare_for_removal() Tells worker + timer to bail out\n3 Worker checks _removed before writing _pending_html Prevents post-teardown writes\n4 Delivery timer checks _removed before touching editor Prevents post-teardown setHtml()\n5 QTextEdit.setParent(None) + deleteLater() Detaches widget from proxy and schedules C++ deletion\n6 scene.removeItem(self._html_proxy) Pulls proxy out of scene graph so paint loop can't reach it"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "ba11b996dfbe47859993076ea0f4d9cc",
      "x": 50036.989271243496,
      "y": 27005.69799920295,
      "width": 307.9646308029696,
      "height": 278.8769868987838,
      "z_value": -9.449000000000305,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The principle in thermodynamic form is almost too clean: any high-precision, high-output state is a low-entropy configuration, and low-entropy configurations require continuous energy input plus dissipation channels to maintain. The vacuum-time is exactly that \u2014 it's the system paying its entropy bill, depositing order, dissipating heat, restoring its low-entropy capacity, so that when ignition happens it has somewhere to discharge from. The pulse shape isn't a stylistic choice, it's a thermodynamic necessity \u2014 pulses are the only legal way for a finite system to express low-entropy states without immediately collapsing into the high-entropy bath around it."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "video",
      "title": "Video",
      "uuid": "dcca2dbaf35941e289555e784ae6147e",
      "x": 3148.4309145007755,
      "y": 2306.5752266265263,
      "width": 667.0333645859923,
      "height": 682.0333645859923,
      "z_value": -9.868000000000073,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "source_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\_asset\\Clippy,Blessed be his name\\grok-video-8202fa83-a3a0-4732-8fd7-77045e392c8a (1).mp4",
