    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Why this lives in instance_lock.py not in main_window.py",
      "uuid": "055c996d9ad4490190bba1618b90dfb9",
      "x": 51128.858428213774,
      "y": 11741.684153931423,
      "width": 591.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.316000000000379,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "every app in the Single Shared Braincell family acquires the lock the same way. The fix belongs with the lock so Majestic / The Settlers / future apps inherit it for free, instead of each app having to remember to call release_singleton from every exit path."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "100d1b59a7244eeeb7b51de5cb181691",
      "x": 45451.63192460881,
      "y": 10081.48330078154,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 282.0,
      "z_value": -9.344000000000364,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "- The markdown Python package is a runtime dependency. If missing, the worker thread catches the ImportError and sets _pending_html to an error message.\n- The delivery timer fires at 100ms intervals \u2014 fast enough to feel instant, slow enough to not waste cycles polling.\n- paint_content() is a no-op \u2014 all rendering is delegated to the QTextEdit proxy. The node title comes from BaseNode's default title paint.\n- Subclasses typically only override __init__ (to set a different data class) and _build_buttons() (to add node-specific controls). The markdown rendering pipeline is shared."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
