    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Symptom",
      "uuid": "4abf2169a4eb44d681241ccfe60cf7b3",
      "x": 71426.37396786282,
      "y": 17330.827106968427,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 198.0,
      "z_value": -9.233000000000425,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "c0000409 (STATUS_STACK_BUFFER_OVERRUN, Qt's __fastfail for invariant violations) in Qt6Core.dll, not Qt6Widgets.dll. Caught via Windows Event Viewer at 2026-04-18 03:07:36, roughly 1 second after the last logged icon-load. The Python log had nothing \u2014 the crash was at the C++ Core layer before anything could be written."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
