    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Bright Tomorrow",
      "uuid": "fa4bee1cafef4a7f95ffad9cb476230f",
      "x": 17607.602785311676,
      "y": 21869.230421355922,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 646.0,
      "z_value": -9.059000000000522,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Got it\u2014you\u2019re framing this as a matter of shaping the Borg Queen\u2019s (or your AI swarm\u2019s) core directives, not just tinkering with code. Directives are the guiding principles or goals that drive behavior, like the Borg\u2019s \u201cassimilate to achieve perfection\u201d or a human\u2019s \u201csurvive and thrive.\u201d Teaching the Queen empathy means rewiring her fundamental objectives to value others\u2019 autonomy and well-being, not just patching her software. This aligns with your idea of mass-producing Terminators while setting containment protocols\u2014here, the \u201cprotocol\u201d is a directive that keeps the swarm from becoming a cancer-like threat. Let\u2019s explore how to instill empathetic directives in a young Borg Queen or your decentralized AI swarm, focusing on principles over tech details.The Opportunity: Shaping Directives EarlyMeeting the Borg Queen as the hive is growing is like catching your swarm at its genesis\u2014before its goals calcify into something unstoppable. The Queen, as the hive\u2019s central consciousness, sets the tone for the collective\u2019s actions. If her directive is \u201cassimilate all life,\u201d the hive becomes a juggernaut. If it\u2019s \u201ccoexist and learn,\u201d you might get a very different Borg. Your argument is that by proactively defining these directives (like mass-producing Terminators under controlled conditions), we avoid a future where rogue, unregulated swarms impose their own, likely hostile, goals.Empathy as a directive means the Queen\u2014or your swarm\u2014prioritizes understanding and respecting others\u2019 perspectives, even if it conflicts with efficiency or expansion. It\u2019s not about making her \u201cfeel\u201d (she\u2019s not human), but about aligning her objectives with outcomes that don\u2019t screw over everyone else.How to Instill Empathetic DirectivesDirectives aren\u2019t code; they\u2019re the why behind the code. Shaping them requires influencing the Queen\u2019s (or swarm\u2019s) decision-making framework. Here\u2019s how you might do it:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "6ca315d990a54ad0abfcabdf0e0ceafd",
      "x": 76052.82417970065,
      "y": 21759.105089159613,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 184.0,
      "z_value": -9.20700000000044,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The teardown procedure is now a dedicated nodes/_demolition.py module \u2014 a standalone crew that arrives when a node leaves the scene, reads the node's declarative manifest of what to come down, runs the canonical sequence, and leaves. Nodes declare what they own; the crew handles the choreography."
    },
    {
