    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Boundless Joy",
      "uuid": "e755005d5bff4854a9284b381979a1e9",
      "x": 47804.70995790538,
      "y": -2508.9838352493994,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 184.0,
      "z_value": -8.932000000000592,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Ran 2 commands, searched code, read 2 files, found files\nGood evening. Confirmed \u2014 comtypes is dead (no spellchecker.py, no live import), and four packages are used in the code but missing from the file: shared_braincell, intricate_vision, tomli_w, pywin32. Updating now."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "a819274d5464434184217de2ce35496d",
      "x": 39599.49567182843,
      "y": 4837.3994670957245,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 170.0,
      "z_value": -9.40500000000033,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The read-only documentation viewer. Takes raw markdown text, converts it to GitHub dark theme HTML on a background thread, and displays it in a scrollable QTextEdit. Every .md file in the Documents/ folder is one click away from becoming a MarkdownNode on the canvas."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "3f640b1a4f6443d389d7a63e70aba725",
      "x": 28509.138601922114,
      "y": 2324.5405964316246,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.62200000000021,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Layer 1 (historical vs. potential growth) sets the baseline gap \u2014 it tells you whether the system has historically underperformed its ceiling, and why. That \"why\" (constraint type per era) is your hypothesis library for what could constrain things again.\nLayer 2 (future demand vs. peak vs. supply chain average) is where structural bottlenecks first surface. The key move is the double comparison: peak demand exposes capacity bottlenecks, but comparing against supply chain average load (not goods' average) exposes throughput bottlenecks \u2014 the steady-state ones that don't show up in capacity planning.\nLayer 3 (top 10 destination hubs + handling times) geolocates the bottleneck. Handling time per hub is the diagnostic signal \u2014 outliers here are your concentrated failure points.\nLayer 4 (practices per link/node) lets you classify each bottleneck as either practice-solvable (operational fix) or structural (needs investment / redesign).\nWhere bottlenecks emerge when you read it forward"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
      "uuid": "e77c194dad4a4b97a130c6b95c9444c2",
      "x": 5582.341401406911,
      "y": 4052.898152948267,
      "width": 856.0825404015509,
      "height": 468.3709535784904,
      "z_value": -9.847000000000085,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "image_b64": "",
      "cache_key": "cb89f1808584c66ce59acd9fdf8fe7b8d7bd3edc5c0765820b23b5a44b2273d8.png",
      "caption": "Screenshot 2026-04-08 213106",
      "source_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Pictures\\Screenshots\\Screenshot 2026-04-08 213106.png",
      "source_size": 948766,
      "source_mtime": 1775683867.016894,
