      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -9.22500000000043,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The button-driven _split_into_nodes call on a live MarkdownNode is unaffected \u2014 only the zombie-spawn caller in the Info sidebar quiets the machinery, because only that caller disposes the node afterward."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "fa875c243e494f82afc8298de52f0b1d",
      "x": 28980.922516429444,
      "y": 3422.3504279041235,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.619000000000211,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The useful question at each layer is: \"What does this layer reveal that the previous one couldn't?\" If a bottleneck only shows up at Layer 3, it's geographic/node-specific. If it shows up at Layer 2 already, it's systemic. That distinction drives whether you fix it with local intervention or chain-wide redesign."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "0a578de6112e4e9eb8f82f1a1425f534",
      "x": 49870.698968714,
      "y": 24125.192028673595,
      "width": 318.27321822640806,
      "height": 284.1431212328753,
      "z_value": -9.4580000000003,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "And the imitators' silliness becomes structurally identifiable now: they're looking at the ignition window and concluding that's the whole organism. They see the rocket at T+3 seconds and try to build something that does what the rocket is doing at T+3 seconds, missing that what the rocket is doing at T+3 seconds is spending something it took five years to accumulate. They see Bolt at the 60-meter mark and try to train that, missing that the 60-meter mark is the expression of fifteen years of substrate preparation that's invisible because it doesn't look like running. Trying to copy the visible output isn't just inefficient \u2014 it's category-incorrect. You can't copy a discharge by studying the spark; you have to build the capacitor."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
