      "body_text": "The recursion question I asked earlier \u2014 how you detect when the reflex itself needs updating \u2014 is now sharper, because everything you just said implies the reflex can't be updated incrementally without compromising the very integrity that makes it work. So either updates require a partial re-installation cycle at the same inhumane pace, or there's some auditing layer running on top that I haven't heard you describe yet. Which one is it?"
