      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Good",
      "uuid": "1802a2cb035a463f90b30f55f17612bd",
      "x": 10722.614390994397,
      "y": 4288.641237366173,
      "width": 282.55159146239833,
      "height": 180.66700505307654,
      "z_value": -9.955000000000025,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The Five never received\nThe context of understanding from The One\n\nWhat five received\nwas the contextual abstraction\nThat The Three needed\nTo make sense of it in the first place\nIn it's own context"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "723688e30e1f4f46a336c0ea1afe4587",
      "x": 93237.88425751698,
      "y": 29276.379670451053,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 212.0,
      "z_value": -9.128000000000483,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "- HealthNode._poll_gc \u2014 reworked to use the helper\n- ClaudeInfoNode._kick_scan\n- JoyStatsNode._refresh\n- PerfNode._refresh\n- LogNode._refresh\n- VideoNode._check_cache_delivery \u2014 supersedes the narrower _destroyed probe\n- MergeNode._sync_list"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "695fea4fbe464c86bebd469bc6cc90c5",
      "x": 94620.64894183549,
      "y": 30216.54801529836,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 352.0,
      "z_value": -9.122000000000487,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1. _shake_delete spawns 8,000 particles and defers removeItem.\n2. Peer Connection glide timers continue ticking at 60Hz against the still-present-but-soon-to-be-severed wire.\n3. _deferred_remove fires on the next event-loop tick \u2192 itemChange \u2192 _prepare_for_removal \u2192 demolition crew runs all five phases.  Phase 0 zeroes flags and invalidates the scene rect (1337px wide for the extreme case, blanketing dozens of peers).\n4. A concurrent Connection glide tick or NodeBehaviour pulse on a surviving peer dereferences the dying node's rect / pos / state in the sub-millisecond window between phase 0 zeroing the geometry and the Qt paint loop re-entering.\n5. Stack cookie fails on the C runtime call, __fastfail \u2192 0xC0000409."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "385d98adac9c4deeb46f68032487b45b",
      "x": 94271.81068284642,
      "y": 29988.38408211545,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -9.123000000000486,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "For isolated single-node deletions this is fine \u2014 the paint scheduler absorbs a small peer cascade without racing.  But when the deleted node sits inside a long chain of wires (the 100+ AboutNode checklist chain):"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "The 1-2-3-4-5",
      "uuid": "3ba3887e51c54743ac30a980b8d45492",
      "x": 10518.551416194761,
      "y": 207.58929178356857,
      "width": 304.1953855428355,
      "height": 300.5065914199974,
      "z_value": -9.999,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Not like it's that other time when the idiot kept running to her and asking her questions about me and she had a near panic attack over who this rude monster was and freaked out.\n\nAnd then the idiot came back to me to tell me that she doesn't like me and had just totally freaked out when he mentioned me.\n\nThen later when me and her where talking we kept wondering who that idiot was and neither of us having the slightest idea why he was running between us.\n\nNah... the fact of the matter is neither of us like him, I responded the same way when you came tell me you have been harassing her didn't I ?"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Final state of _check_delivery()",
