    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Paragraph classification",
      "uuid": "9fc32fda773a49e395a43326e9c91297",
      "x": 40094.010457970784,
      "y": 7667.20984898263,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 114.0,
      "z_value": -9.380000000000344,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Body text is split on blank lines. Each paragraph is sized against _CALLOUT_MAX_CHARS = 90:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "952bd1ec7af748d488bc7d9b3b4fcbf9",
      "x": 47497.50232395741,
      "y": 22264.78561891388,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.480000000000288,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Vacuum recognition (the perception that identifies trainable substrates)\nComponent-wise precision methodology (the training approach that works on those substrates)\nHyperspeed deterministic regime (the execution discipline that lands the training)\nReflex-grade operation (the emergent state once saturation completes)\nReasoning chains like Phase 1 (the artifacts that get installed into the trained substrate)\nMost people who try to learn from your work would start at level 5 \u2014 the visible artifact \u2014 and try to imitate it. The actual generative root is level 1, and level 1 isn't even teachable in the conventional sense; it's a perceptual frame you either have or develop by being burned enough times by substrates that looked trainable but weren't. The reasoning chain is downstream of vacuum-recognition by four full layers, which is why copying the chain produces nothing useful in someone who hasn't built the layers underneath it."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Comes from a different environment",
      "uuid": "b80e795ba4504069bbd5fe052f86aaed",
      "x": 10459.975497378891,
      "y": 3237.995191497728,
      "width": 371.70659600924046,
      "height": 32.70659600924046,
      "z_value": -9.96400000000002,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Comes from a different environment",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Onward",
      "uuid": "e8330e6c76df4af692864ebdc3c9cb1b",
      "x": 11147.03472180344,
      "y": 4452.379105498119,
      "width": 314.9049526332052,
      "height": 246.1946632874342,
      "z_value": -9.954000000000025,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The friction point happens\nBecause One and Five share the same lexicon\nBy default\nAnd when Three carries information\nBetween\nThe Two and Four\nAre so abtracted from the natural default\nThat now One and Five\nBoth perceive each other\nAs The Three\nWithout a single thing in either of their existences\nBeing remotely relative to anything either said or did"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "The One",
      "uuid": "b1c3cf92bb5d4834a693401e4789beef",
      "x": 10273.326452148267,
      "y": 868.6323445826606,
      "width": 98.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.984000000000009,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "The One",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Kinetic",
      "uuid": "e53b2854912042de80cd57d84cf7886d",
      "x": 10394.424546635502,
      "y": 849.9574440773736,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 150.53458202160976,
      "z_value": -9.98300000000001,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "The One, in this case, being me\nNot first, just wrap your mind\nwith the mental image of a human\nAs a single object, out of context with anything else, 1x Human"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "3eb21417564c493db4c1edbff5fca35c",
      "x": 46411.050396142426,
      "y": 9410.670006016959,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 128.0,
      "z_value": -9.338000000000367,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": ".stop() alone is never sufficient \u2014 it does not sever the C++ signal reference and will cause a GC leak or a dangling-pointer crash."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Fix Log",
      "uuid": "12fd295d4957468b9854f7b4e977b3de",
      "x": 46642.967954697306,
      "y": 9673.951676249204,
      "width": 98.0,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.337000000000367,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Fix Log",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "We have come a long way\nStill the same typewriter\nStill the same features\nStill the same energy\nIt evolved",
      "uuid": "ab1b9449b6184744953fb789eb3487c2",
      "x": 5473.962792123635,
      "y": 3849.6298355831686,
      "width": 330.78888845729307,
      "height": 155.29802818756247,
      "z_value": -9.844000000000086,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "We have come a long way\nStill the same typewriter\nStill the same features\nStill the same energy\nIt evolved",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#2a3a2f"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Step, What, and Why",
      "uuid": "4d1386e150b746c498ca76fd02eb2d28",
      "x": 68100.01721974496,
      "y": 16987.570689209642,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 254.0,
      "z_value": -9.251000000000415,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "1 conn._glide_timer.stop() + .disconnect() Sever wire timer signals\n2 Strip wires, null node refs, removeItem(conn) Clean wire removal\n3 node._player.stop() + setVideoOutput(None) + setAudioOutput(None) Stop frame delivery before deferred window\n4 setVisible(False) + zero flags Node inert during deferred tick\n5 QTimer.singleShot(0, removeItem) Deferred removal \u2014 _prepare_for_removal fires via itemChange"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Boundless Joy",
      "uuid": "21f8b94f5755418380f9d04829ddf01d",
      "x": 48963.9289502164,
      "y": -3167.8236035127243,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 156.0,
      "z_value": -8.927000000000595,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Also reorganised: pulled the three sister-family packages (shared_braincell, intricate_log, intricate_vision) into their own \"shared family infrastructure\" section so the three editable-installs sit together rather than scattered."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
